============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Categorical Imperative
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Act only on principles you could will to be universal laws
Philosopher:  Immanuel Kant
Example:      Don't lie; if universal lying existed, language would break down

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Rationalism
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Some knowledge is innate or derivable by reason alone
Philosopher:  Descartes/Spinoza
Example:      Math truths like 2+2=4 are known by reason, not experiment

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

Theorem/Law:  Nash Equilibrium
Branch:       Game Theory
Formula:      No player benefits from unilateral strategy change
Applications: Economics, AI, political science
Discoverer:   John Nash (1950)

